http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: Wisconsin's Model Academic Standards for Personal Financial Literacy

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Wisconsin's Model Academic Standards for Personal Financial Literacy are similar to previously established model academic standards that set forth the knowledge, skills, and attitudes students need in order to be successful. The personal financial literacy standards add a rigor and relevance framework in order to illustrate how knowledge grows/spirals with experience and practice.
Relating Income and Education
Students in Wisconsin will understand the relationship between education, income, career, and desired lifestyle and will develop the planning skills needed to achieve desired financial goals.
